This is a sample console application I use for rough testing and playing and once the lib is somewhat stable it'll be used to demonstrate some features..

On my machine I've told git to ignore further changes the corresponding app.config/settings files like that:
	
	git update-index --assume-unchanged Program.cs
	git update-index --assume-unchanged app.config
	git update-index --assume-unchanged Properties/Settings.*

In order to reverse this, you can simply use the command '--no-assume-unchanged' instead of '--assume-unchanged' (see http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4114163/how-to-tell-git-to-ignore-all-further-edit-to-a-single-file-without-removing-it-f)